{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d458-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s794"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"794"},"text":"§ 794.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Gathering or delivering defense information to aid foreign government","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d459-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s794/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Whoever, with intent or reason to believe that it is to be used to the injury of the United States or to the advantage of a foreign nation, communicates, delivers, or transmits, or attempts to communicate, deliver, or transmit, to any foreign government, or to any faction or party or military or naval force within a foreign country, whether recognized or unrecognized by the United States, or to any representative, officer, agent, employee, subject, or citizen thereof, either directly or indirectly, any document, writing, code book, signal book, sketch, photograph, photographic negative, blueprint, plan, map, model, note, instrument, appliance, or information relating to the national defense, shall be punished by death or by imprisonment for any term of years or for life, except that the sentence of death shall not be imposed unless the jury or, if there is no jury, the court, further finds that the offense resulted in the identification by a foreign power (as defined in section 101(a) of the Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Act of 1978) of an individual acting as an agent of the United States and consequently in the death of that individual, or directly concerned nuclear weaponry, military spacecraft or satellites, early warning systems, or other means of defense or retaliation against large-scale attack; war plans; communications intelligence or cryptographic information; or any other major weapons system or major element of defense strategy.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d45a-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s794/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Whoever, in time of war, with intent that the same shall be communicated to the enemy, collects, records, publishes, or communicates, or attempts to elicit any information with respect to the movement, numbers, description, condition, or disposition of any of the Armed Forces, ships, aircraft, or war materials of the United States, or with respect to the plans or conduct, or supposed plans or conduct of any naval or military operations, or with respect to any works or measures undertaken for or connected with, or intended for the fortification or defense of any place, or any other information relating to the public defense, which might be useful to the enemy, shall be punished by death or by imprisonment for any term of years or for life.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d45b-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s794/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If two or more persons conspire to violate this section, and one or more of such persons do any act to effect the object of the conspiracy, each of the parties to such conspiracy shall be subject to the punishment provided for the offense which is the object of such conspiracy.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d45c-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s794/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d45d-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s794/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Any person convicted of a violation of this section shall forfeit to the United States irrespective of any provision of State law—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d45e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s794/d/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any property constituting, or derived from, any proceeds the person obtained, directly or indirectly, as the result of such violation, and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d45f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s794/d/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any of the person’s property used, or intended to be used, in any manner or part, to commit, or to facilitate the commission of, such violation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"For the purposes of this subsection, the term “State” includes a State of the United States, the District of Columbia, and any commonwealth, territory, or possession of the United States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d460-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s794/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The court, in imposing sentence on a defendant for a conviction of a violation of this section, shall order that the defendant forfeit to the United States all property described in paragraph (1) of this subsection.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d461-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s794/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The provisions of subsections (b), (c) and (e) through (p) of section 413 of the Comprehensive Drug Abuse Prevention and Control Act of 1970 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s853/b"},"text":"21 U.S.C. 853(b)","children":[],"tail":", (c), and (e)–(p)) shall apply to—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d462-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s794/d/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" property subject to forfeiture under this subsection;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d463-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s794/d/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any seizure or disposition of such property; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d464-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s794/d/3/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any administrative or judicial proceeding in relation to such property,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"if not inconsistent with this subsection.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d465-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s794/d/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Notwithstanding ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s524/c"},"text":"section 524(c) of title 28","children":[],"tail":", there shall be deposited in the Crime Victims Fund in the Treasury all amounts from the forfeiture of property under this subsection remaining after the payment of expenses for forfeiture and sale authorized by law."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d466-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 645","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/737"},"text":"62 Stat. 737","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-09-03/ch1261"},"text":"Sept. 3, 1954, ch. 1261","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 201, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68/1219"},"text":"68 Stat. 1219","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/399/tXIII/s1306/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–399, title XIII, § 1306(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-08-27"},"text":"Aug. 27, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/898"},"text":"100 Stat. 898","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/690/tVII/s7064"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–690, title VII, § 7064","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-18"},"text":"Nov. 18, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/4404"},"text":"102 Stat. 4404","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/322/tVI/s60003/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–322, title VI, § 60003(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/1968"},"text":"108 Stat. 1968","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/359/tVIII/s804/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–359, title VIII, § 804(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-14"},"text":"Oct. 14, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/3440"},"text":"108 Stat. 3440","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/294/tVI"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–294, title VI","children":[],"tail":", §§ 604(b)(2), 607(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-11"},"text":"Oct. 11, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/3506"},"text":"110 Stat. 3506","children":[],"tail":", 3511.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb8e0d467-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb8e0d468-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on sections 32 and 34 of title 50, U.S.C., 1940 ed., War and National Defense (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1917-06-15/ch30"},"text":"June 15, 1917, ch. 30","children":[],"tail":", title I, §§ 2, 4, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/40/218"},"text":"40 Stat. 218","children":[],"tail":", 219)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section consolidates sections 32 and 34 of title 50, U.S.C., 1940 ed., War and National Defense.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The words “or induces or aids another” were omitted as unnecessary in view of definition of “principal” in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s2"},"text":"section 2 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The conspiracy provision of said section 34 was also incorporated in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s2388"},"text":"section 2388 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Minor changes were made in phraseology.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb8e0d469-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idb8e0d46a-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 101(a) of the Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Act of 1978, referred to in subsec. (a), is classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s1801/a"},"text":"section 1801(a) of Title 50","children":[],"tail":", War and National Defense."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb8e0d46b-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/294/s604/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–294, § 604(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", amended directory language of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/322/s60003/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–322, § 60003(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":". See 1994 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/294/s607/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–294, § 607(b)","children":[],"tail":", inserted at end “For the purposes of this subsection, the term ‘State’ includes a State of the United States, the District of Columbia, and any commonwealth, territory, or possession of the United States.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/322"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–322","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/294/s604/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–294, § 604(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted for period at end “, except that the sentence of death shall not be imposed unless the jury or, if there is no jury, the court, further finds that the offense resulted in the identification by a foreign power (as defined in section 101(a) of the Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Act of 1978) of an individual acting as an agent of the United States and consequently in the death of that individual, or directly concerned nuclear weaponry, military spacecraft or satellites, early warning systems, or other means of defense or retaliation against large-scale attack; war plans; communications intelligence or cryptographic information; or any other major weapons system or major element of defense strategy.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/359"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–359","children":[],"tail":" substituted “(p)” for “("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"tail":")” in two places."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsec. (d)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/690"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–690","children":[],"tail":" substituted “amounts” for “amount”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/399"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–399","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1954—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1954-09-03"},"text":"Sept. 3, 1954","children":[],"tail":", increased the penalty for peacetime espionage and corrected a deficiency on the sentencing authority by increasing penalty to death or imprisonment for any term of years."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb8e0d46c-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb8e0d46d-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1996 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/294/s604/b/2"},"text":"section 604(b)(2) of Pub. L. 104–294","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/294/s604/d"},"text":"section 604(d) of Pub. L. 104–294","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s13"},"text":"section 13 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb8e0d46e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Temporary Extension of Section","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Temporary extension of section, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s798"},"text":"section 798 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1953-06-30/ch175/s7"},"text":"Act June 30, 1953, ch. 175, § 7","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/67/133"},"text":"67 Stat. 133","children":[],"tail":", repealed Joint Res. "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-07-03/ch570/s1/a/29"},"text":"July 3, 1952, ch. 570, § 1(a)(29)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/333"},"text":"66 Stat. 333","children":[],"tail":"; Joint Res. "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1953-03-31/ch13/s1"},"text":"Mar. 31, 1953, ch. 13, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/67/18"},"text":"67 Stat. 18","children":[],"tail":", which had provided that this section should continue in force until six months after the termination of the National emergency proclaimed by 1950 Proc. No. 2914 which is set out as a note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s1"},"text":"section 1 of Title 50","children":[],"tail":", War and National Defense."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Joint Res. ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-07-03/ch570/s6"},"text":"July 3, 1952, ch. 570, § 6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/334"},"text":"66 Stat. 334","children":[],"tail":", repealed Joint Res. "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-04-14/ch204"},"text":"Apr. 14, 1952, ch. 204","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/54"},"text":"66 Stat. 54","children":[],"tail":", as amended by Joint Res. "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-05-28/ch339"},"text":"May 28, 1952, ch. 339","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/96"},"text":"66 Stat. 96","children":[],"tail":". Intermediate extensions by Joint Res. "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-06-14/ch437"},"text":"June 14, 1952, ch. 437","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/137"},"text":"66 Stat. 137","children":[],"tail":", and Joint Res. "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-06-30/ch526"},"text":"June 30, 1952, ch. 526","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/296"},"text":"66 Stat. 296","children":[],"tail":", which continued provisions until "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1952-07-03"},"text":"July 3, 1952","children":[],"tail":", expired by their own terms."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb8e0d46f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Indictment for Violating This Section; Limitation Period","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Limitation period in connection with indictments for violating this section, see note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s792"},"text":"section 792 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
